Movie director Jonathan Demme died in New York on Wednesday morning surrounded by his family. NEW YORK - Movie director Jonathan Demme, best known for The Silence of the Lambs has died at the age of 73, his publicist said on Wednesday.Demme, who also directed the Oscar winning film Philadelphia was suffering from esophageal cancer, publicist Annalee Paulo said in a statement. She said he died in New York on Wednesday morning surrounded by his family.Demme's most recent film was the 2015 comedy Ricki and the Flash, starring Meryl Streep as an ageing rocker.New York-born Demme won the directing Oscar for the 1991 thriller The Silence of the Lambs, which also won Oscars for best picture and for its stars Anthony Hopkins and Jodie Foster.